I'm using the latest version of VS Code on OS X (Version 0.10.8 (0.10.8), db71ac615ddf9f33b133ff2536f5d33a77d4774e).

Replication steps:
Paste the following into a new whatever.ts file.

```
function foo() { }
function bar() { }
function baz() { }

export {
foo,
bar,
baz
};
```

Now highlight the properties of the export (the 3 lines saying foo, bar, baz) and press tab to indent them and it outputs the following and can't be undone using the undo command:

```
function foo() { }
function bar() { }
function baz() { }

export {
    az
};
```

The indenting seems to happen but where did my exports go?! :open_mouth:
